for_developers/README.md
     1Рєњ# For developers
     3РєњWhile `mdbook` is mainly used as a command line tool, you can also import the
     4Рєњunderlying libraries directly and use those to manage a book. It also has a fairly
     5Рєњflexible plugin mechanism, allowing you to create your own custom tooling and
     6Рєњconsumers (often referred to as *backends*) if you need to do some analysis of
     7Рєњthe book or render it in a different format.
     8Рєњ
     9РєњThe *For Developers* chapters are here to show you the more advanced usage of
    10Рєњ`mdbook`.
    11Рєњ
    12РєњThe two main ways a developer can hook into the book's build process is via,
    13Рєњ
    14Рєњ- [Preprocessors](preprocessors.md)
    15Рєњ- [Alternative Backends](backends.md)
    16Рєњ
    17Рєњ## The build process
    19РєњThe process of rendering a book project goes through several steps.
    20Рєњ
    21Рєњ1. Load the book
    22Рєњ    - Parse the `book.toml`, falling back to the default `Config` if it doesn't
    23Рєњ       exist
      РєњРђд
    30Рєњ## Using `mdbook` as a library
    32РєњThe `mdbook` binary is just a wrapper around the underlying mdBook crates,
    33Рєњexposing their functionality as a command-line program. If you want to
    34Рєњprogrammatically drive mdBook, you can use the [`mdbook-driver`] crate.
    35РєњThis can be used to add your own functionality or tweak the build process.
    36Рєњ
      РєњРђд
for_developers/backends.md
     1Рєњ# Alternative backends
     3РєњA "backend" is simply a program which `mdbook` will invoke during the book
     4Рєњrendering process. This program is passed a JSON representation of the book and
     5Рєњconfiguration information via `stdin`. Once the backend receives this
     6Рєњinformation it is free to do whatever it wants.
     7Рєњ
     8РєњSee [Configuring Renderers](../format/configuration/renderers.md) for more information about using backends.
     9Рєњ
    10РєњThe community has developed several backends.
      РєњРђд
    13Рєњ## Setting up Рђд
    53Рєњ## Inspecting the book Рђд
    82Рєњ## Enabling the backend Рђд
   159Рєњ## Configuration Рђд
   219Рєњ## Output and signalling failure Рђд
   322Рєњ## Wrapping up Рђд
